{"ts":"2026-06-27T04:26:56.235Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Defining the Key Page**\n\nOkay, I've confirmed that `PrivatePageHeader` perfectly fits the bill. Now, I'm shifting my focus to designing the `/portal/documents` page. It's becoming clear that this will be a premium document library specifically for clients. The instructions are clear that the landing page is off-limits and that I should include [omitted for brevity].\n\n\n**Planning the `/portal/documents` page**\n\nI'm now deep in the design phase for the `/portal/documents` page. My focus is on ensuring excellent mobile performance while integrating features like search, category filtering (Proposals, SOW, etc.), project filters, document type filters, and status filters. I envision a layout switcher allowing users to toggle between Bento Cards Grid and Table display, and the interface will be a preview-only environment with a metadata drawer. I've run lint and build.\n\n\n**Designing the Repository**\n\nI'm now honing in on the interactive components, specifically the filter blocks, aiming for a clean, intuitive design. I'm leaning toward a high-contrast aesthetic with subtle neon accents. A \"No files found\" state is essential. Furthermore, interactive drawers will showcase comprehensive cryptographic metadata.\n\nI'm now crafting a visual metaphor of a cryptographic vault, complete with strict access controls. Each document will bear a unique SHA-256 hash and a \"Confidentiality Clearance Level\" badge. The aim is to match GFF AI's high-tech, sovereign atmosphere.\n\nI'm planning the layout using a standard PrivatePageHeader titled \"Document Repository & Seals\" with a badge \"SECURE_VAULT.\" I'm including quick metrics, such as total documents.\n\n\n**Refining the Filter Row**\n\nI'm currently focused on the horizontal filter panel, aiming for intuitive interactions. The panel includes a search input with clear controls, and category, project, document type, and status selects. A \"Clear All Filters\" button will appear dynamically. Finally, I'm integrating toggle buttons for card and table view layouts.\n\n\n**Detailing the Metadata**\n\nI'm now detailing document metadata. I'll include attributes like Title, Category, Type, Status, Version, Owner, Visibility, File Size, Uploaded At, and SHA-256 Hash. I'm also planning a simulated \"Verify Certificate Security\" live terminal logger for visual validation. This will be alongside a close button, with clear warnings about disabled download/upload in telemetry mode.\n\n**Planning the User Interface**\n\nI'm now planning the user interaction strategy. This includes a fluid layout switcher, live search and multi-dimensional filtering, and a clear filters button. There will also be an interactive document drawer with a sliding animation, background dimming, hash copying, and simulated AMD SEV-SNP attestation telemetry.\n\n**Focusing on Mobile Design**\n\nFinally, I'm now fully focused on mobile responsiveness, which includes responsive filters that stack or drop-down on smaller screens. Cards will wrap naturally, and the table will resize fluidly.\n\n\n"}}
